OL,3,CHow to spot a shooting star in
OL,4,Ctonight's Quadrantid meteor shower
OL,6,FMeteors are the result of small
OL,7,Fparticles from space entering the
OL,8,FEarth's atmosphere at high speed. The
OL,9,Fsuperheated air around the meteor
OL,10,Fglows briefly, and is visible from the
OL,11,Fground as a streak of light known as a
OL,12,F"shooting star".
OL,14,FAs the Quadrantids crash into the
OL,15,Fatmosphere, they will travel at around
OL,16,F40km per second. The meteor shower is
OL,17,Fmade up of debris from the asteroid
OL,18,F2003 EH1.
