OL,3,CHow to spot a shooting star in
OL,4,Ctonight's Quadrantid meteor shower
OL,6,FDr Robert Massey, deputy director of
OL,7,Fthe Royal Astronomical Society, said
OL,8,Fthe key for anyone hoping to catch a
OL,9,Fglimpse of the Quadrantids is to move
OL,10,Fas far away from light pollution as
OL,11,Fpossible.
OL,13,FHe said: "They won't be the brightest
OL,14,Fmeteors on the whole, but they do
OL,15,Finclude a fair number of fireballs. A
OL,16,Ffireball is a dramatic sounding thing,
OL,17,Fbut what it really means is a really
OL,18,Fbright meteor.
