OL,3,CHow to spot a shooting star in
OL,4,Ctonight's Quadrantid meteor shower
OL,6,FDr Massey said: "You're unlikely to
OL,7,Fcatch anything (with a phone) because
OL,8,Fthey're so fleeting ` they only last
OL,9,Fperhaps a fraction of a second ` so
OL,10,Fyour reactions are not going to be
OL,11,Fgood enough to photograph it. So what
OL,12,Fpeople tend to do is what are called
OL,13,Flong exposures.
OL,15,F"They open up the lens or the shutter
OL,16,Fand leave it running for several
OL,17,Fminutes, or anything up to half an
OL,18,Fhour."
